    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect signaling procedure sequence in nrue_init_openair0\n\n### Summary\nThe function `nrue_init_openair0` in `executables/nr-ue-ru.c` had an incorrect signaling procedure sequence that violated 3GPP message flow downstream. This caused RRC connection establishment failures in some scenarios.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running the NR UE with specific timing conditions, the UE would fail to properly establish RRC connection with the gNB. Symptoms include:\n- RRC setup failure messages in the logs\n- UE getting stuck in IDLE state\n- No PDU sessions being established\n\nThis occurs because the RRC/NAS tasks were being created after the UE threads were started, causing a race condition where signaling messages could be processed before the RRC/NAS handlers were ready.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/nr-uesoftmodem.c`: Moved `create_tasks_nrue()` call before `init_NR_UE_threads()` to ensure proper signaling sequence\n- Added explanatory comment about the ordering requirement\n"
}